<strong>A QUESTION OF </strong>is a company selling organic fair trade fashion T-shirts produced in Tanzania, Africa. The T-shirts are made under sustainable working conditions, and the employees receive fair wages, English classes, and training in health issues. At A QUESTION OF we are striving to link CSR, creativity, and fashion trends with great T-shirt design, to create value for both our customers and for the textile workers in Tanzania <a href="[~6~]"><strong>Click here</strong></a></p>
<p>A QUESTION OF T-shirt designs and prints follow the same design path built on
simplicity and responsibility. We perceive our products as being<em>; "Fashion T-shirts topped with social ethics"</em>. </p>
<p>To view our newest designs visit the webshop <strong><a href="http://www.aquestionofshop.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Click here</strong></a></strong></p>
<p>
Inspired by the increasing trend in social responsibility A QUESTION OF was founded in 2008. Since the beginning A QUESTION OF has been focusing on fair trade and environmentally friendly T-shirt products. This has resulted in a close relationship to a Danida supported factory in Tanzania operating under fair and ethical conditions. The T-shirts fabricated are all made from organic cotton also produced in Africa.<br />
<br />
Today A QUESTION OF is selling design T-shirts and plain T-shirts for both men and women. With our T-shirt products we are tapping into the emerging trends in society and mixing these with creativity and social responsibility. Therefore<strong>, </strong>our T-shirts are highly valued by our customers, and we are continuously striving to improve our offerings. 
